news.title: Gurugram: DTCP to check occupation certificate in phased manner
news.para: Bhatt after attending a meeting with the deputy commissioner on Monday also informed that rules are being violated by constructing several floors on the Economically Weaker Section (EWS) plots in DLF Phase-3.

news.title: Over 52 lakh houses delivered, 83.36 lakh grounded for construction under PMAY-Urban
news.para: According to the ministry, around 9.71 lakh houses have been completed and delivered to beneficiaries in Uttar Pradesh under the PMAY-U, followed by Gujarat (6.22 lakh), Maharashtra (5.26 lakh) and Andhra Pradesh (4.77 lakh).

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body demands Rs 149 crore property tax dues from defunct city mills
news.para: ​​These mills had closed 25 to 30 years ago and the AMC has been raising tax bills every year. Prominent on the list are Calico Mills Ltd, established by the Sarabhai family in 1888, which shut in 1998.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram civic body to conduct property tax adalat from Dec 3
news.para: ​Mayor Arya Rajendran said that 300 complaints have been received so far in response to the updated tax data being published on the corporation website for various wards.

news.title: Pune: Owners' wait for Gunthewari plan launch continues
news.para: “Applications are not being processed now. The works to develop a dedicated software are underway and will be completed soon,” said Yuvraj Deshmukh, a senior official of the Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC).

news.title: NDMC readies plan to redevelop areas around old Delhi railway station
news.para: “Now, we need these properties for carrying out remunerative and other development works. We cancelled the licence deed and asked them to give back possession of the land some time ago,” said a senior official.

news.title: Gujarat HC orders action against high-rises sans fire NOC
news.para: The court said that the authorities should demolish a couple of buildings to set an example, for it is better to put people out of their houses than watching them charred to death.

news.title: Rise in steel, cement prices affects Thiruvananthapuram smart city projects
news.para: The sharp escalation in prices of steel and cement has forced the firms to demand the cost escalation from SCTL. In the past one month, price of steel has gone up by Rs 3,000-3,500 per tonne while 50kg weighing cement sack price increased by Rs 80-100.

news.title: Chandigarh: UT adviser seeks year-wise action plan for solar plant installation
news.para: During a review meeting on Monday, it was observed that many residential houses, industrial buildings, commercial buildings and institutional buildings etc had not complied with the order of mandatory installation of solar power plant in Chandigarh.

news.title: Noida: 1,822 Jal Vayu Vihar residents still don't have voting rights
news.para: The impasse between two sections of residents — one who has voting rights and another who doesn’t — is likely to have a binding effect on the daily operations of the society.

news.title: Gurugram: Violating construction ban to attract heavier penalties
news.para: On rampant unauthorised construction in DLF-3 licenced colony, the deputy commissioner asked the district task force to initiate police action and get FIRs registered against the violators.

news.title: IIFL Home Finance plans expansion, aims to raise up to Rs 1,000 crore
news.para: This time, the lender is looking to issue secured bonds to lower the cost at around 8-9%, significantly lower than its offerings of 9.6-10% in July, people familiar with the matter said.

news.title: Proptech startup Propdial raises Rs 1 crore via debentures
news.para: The fresh capital will be used to grow Propdial’s local business and expansion across India. The company, which helps people manage property remotely, had raised seed funding earlier this year.

news.title: CRISIL Ratings revises Phoenix Mills’ rating outlook to stable
news.para: "The outlook revision reflects a strong recovery in retail sales witnessed across malls in the second quarter ending September and October 2021 post reopening after the second wave of the pandemic and an expected further improvement in retail sales in the second half of 2022," the rating agency said.

news.title: Probe former DHFL brass for causing Rs 40,000 crore loss to lenders: Union Bank to CBI
news.para: In its complaint, the lead bank has affixed the findings of audit firm KPMG, engaged by the consortium, which has prima facie found "deviation of laid down norms and procedures, manipulation of accounts, concealments, undisclosed bank accounts and misrepresentation".
